    "b463: the Human 'Path of Ambition' skill tree grows from 4 skills to 11, adding seven HUMAN-ORIGINAL skills (no more borrowing only dwarf/elf tricks). Combat & willpower: Iron Will (immune to confusion + paralysis), Adrenaline (+6 ATK/+4 DEF below 25% HP), Combat Reflexes (much better initiative), Weapon Master (+3 ATK with any weapon, gear degrades half as fast). Mastery: Veteran (+15% XP on top of Versatility + a depth-scaled bounty on each floor's first kill), Prodigy (extra spell slot + INT cast-gate dropped 13->10 so humans dabble in magic early). Survival: Survivalist (hunger decays half as fast, forage food while walking, and slowly self-repair equipped gear -- un-breaking it). All cost 1 stat point each; the character screen lists all 11 (owned / affordable / locked). Borrowed Stonelore + Wayfarer's Lore kept alongside them. Non-humans unaffected.",
